The paper deals with resource management in a wireless network, specifically in the context of virtual reality and unmanned aerial vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves machine learning algorithms, which suggests a possible category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of virtual reality and image quality and format also suggests a possible category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also deals with spectrum allocation, which suggests a possible category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the use of unmanned aerial vehicles suggests a possible category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
